Ex. No: 12 — Identify and Remove Duplicate Records in a Dataset using Pandas

From the FDS manual

Aim

To identify and remove duplicate records using Pandas.

Theory

Duplicate records may create incorrect analysis.
Pandas provides duplicated() and drop_duplicates() functions to handle duplicates.

Software / Tools Required
•
Python 3.x
•
Anaconda Distribution
•
Jupyter Notebook / IDLE / Google Colab
•
Pandas Library



Program
import pandas as pd

# Creating DataFrame
data = {
    'ID': [101, 102, 102, 103, 104, 104],
    'Name': ['Ravi', 'Anu', 'Anu', 'Kumar', 'Divya', 'Divya'],
    'Marks': [85, 90, 90, 78, 88, 88]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)

print("Original DataFrame:")
print(df)

# Identifying duplicates
print("\nDuplicate Records:")
print(df.duplicated())

# Removing duplicates
clean_df = df.drop_duplicates()

print("\nDataFrame after removing duplicates:")
print(clean_df)


Procedure
Open Jupyter Notebook.
Import Pandas library.
Create DataFrame with duplicate records.
Display original dataset.
Use duplicated() function.
Identify duplicate rows.
Use drop_duplicates().
Remove duplicate records.
Display cleaned dataset.
